text: Kenneth Algernon Black Jr. (December 23, 1932 – January 29, 2019) was an American politician who served in the New Jersey General Assembly from District 3A from 1968 to 1974. He died on January 29, 2019 in Wildwood Crest, New Jersey at age 86. ==References== Category:1932 births Category:2019 deaths Category:Members of the New Jersey General Assembly Category:New Jersey Republicans
title: Kenneth A. Black Jr.
